Chrome and platinum group metals miner Tharisa expects to report a 50% increase in earnings per share (EPS) for the six months ended March 31, at between $0.32 and $0.33. This compares with EPS of $0.21 posted in the prior corresponding six months. Headline earnings per share (HEPS), however, are expected to be between $0.15 and $0.16, which is about 30% lower than the HEPS of $0.22 reported for the six months ended March 31, 2021. The company will release its interim results on or about May 26.